# 2. COMPANY ANALYSIS

## What MUSA Does
Boutique orchestral recording agency that organises and delivers full-service scoring sessions in Prague. MUSA contracts the FILMharmonic Orchestra (its flagship ensemble), provides conductors, engineers, orchestrators, producers, copyists, and handles remote scoring, venues, accommodation, and post-production logistics for international composers and producers.

## Main Services
- Live orchestral recording (full symphony, chamber, ensemble)
- Remote scoring sessions
- Choir & vocalist sessions
- Custom ensemble & soloist contracting
- End-to-end production: conducting, orchestration, engineering, mixing
- Concierge logistics: venues, accommodation, travel, hospitality

## Business Model
B2B service agency. Project-based revenue. Primary clients: composers, music producers, film/TV/game studios, record labels, advertising agencies.

## Market Position
**Premium-craft boutique, mid-tier scale.** Strong artistic reputation, weaker commercial machine. Globally known among veteran composers; nearly invisible to newer generations of composers, indie game studios, library music producers, and modern media buyers.

## Geographic Reach
Global clients, Prague-based delivery. Historical credits span USA, UK, Germany, Denmark, Japan, Canada, Spain, France, Hungary, Brazil, Israel, Lebanon, Korea, China.

## Unique Selling Proposition
*"Hollywood-grade orchestral scoring in Prague. Three decades of credits. One trusted partner. Zero compromise on craft."*

## Brand Tone
**Confident. Cinematic. Craftsman-direct.** Imagine a veteran producer who has run 500+ sessions — calm, experienced, no fluff. The brand should feel like cinema itself: dramatic, well-lit, expensive without being flashy.

## Strengths
1. Exceptional credits portfolio (Red Tails, Halo Wars, Mafia 2, Final Fantasy, Helloween, Sarah Brightman, Celine Dion)
2. Petr Pycha's 25+ years of industry relationships
3. FILMharmonic Orchestra — proprietary, recognised ensemble brand
4. Prague cost advantage — same quality as London/LA, fraction of the cost
5. 100% buyout model — no residuals, no union complexity
6. Full-service delivery — clients coordinate with one team, not ten vendors

## Weaknesses
1. Website is ~12 years out of date in design, UX, SEO, mobile
2. No clear value proposition above the fold
3. No structured inquiry funnel — relies on email/phone
4. Weak SEO — Smecky, Synchron, Budapest Scoring outrank MUSA
5. No content engine — no blog, no behind-the-scenes video, no composer interviews
6. Founder-dependent brand — risks tied to Petr Pycha personally
7. No social proof structure — testimonials, reviews, video testimonials all absent
8. Remote-recording (fastest-growing category) barely visible
9. No multilingual strategy

